sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_assignments
FROM assignments
WHERE course_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(user_id) 
FROM course_enrollment 
WHERE course_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM discussion_forums
WHERE course_id = 1 AND post_text LIKE '%deadline%';

external_knowledge:
- "sailed above the waves of excellence" refers to achieving an average grade greater than 80;
- "high tide mark of 80" is a metaphorical expression for the grade threshold;
- "intrepid voyagers" represents the students who have completed the assignments;
- "challenging seas" symbolizes the assignments.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS distinct_students
FROM course_enrollment
WHERE course_id = 1 AND drop_date IS NULL;
